# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# What is COMMITTED vs IGNORED, and why (reproducibility policy):
#
#  COMMIT: configs/, src/, docs/, paper/, tests/, PREREGISTRATION.md,
#          data/prompts/            <- the FROZEN prompt sets + checksums
#          results/tables/, results/figures/   <- small, and reviewers want them
#          data/pairs/pairs_report.json
#
#  IGNORE: model weights caches, large intermediate generations (regenerable
#          from seeds), virtualenvs, notebook checkpoints.
#
#  data/generations/ and results/judgments/ are BORDERLINE: they are the raw
#  data the protocol says to release (§10 "All raw judgments released as
#  JSONL"). They are small enough for git (a few MB) — so they are committed
#  by default. If your repo grows too big, move them to a GitHub Release or
#  Hugging Face dataset and note the link in README.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/

# Editors / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# Hugging Face / torch caches (never commit weights)
.cache/
hf_cache/

# Notebook noise
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# LaTeX build artifacts
paper/*.aux
paper/*.log
paper/*.out
paper/*.bbl
paper/*.blg
paper/*.synctex.gz
paper/main.pdf

# Scratch
scratch/
*.tmp
